dct_description_sm: Shows coastline of Crooked Island in the Bahamas. Relief shown by hachures; depths shown by soundings. At head of title: Bahamas. "1469." Includes 2 views: Landrail flag staff and Marine Farm flag staff in one. Mark for the anchorage -- Moss House and flag staff as seen from the anchorage. Historic Maps copy has label on verso: 1469, Crooked Island Anchorage.
dct_publisher_sm: London : Published according to Act of Parliament at the Hydrographic Office of the Admiralty ; Sold by R.B. Bate, agent for the Admiralty Charts, 21 Poultry, May 29th. 1843.
